A special tribunal has stopped the controversial Eastern Cape scooter tender in its tracks. eNCA's Aviwe Mtila has more. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A special tribunal has stopped the controversial Eastern Cape scooter tender in its tracks. That is while the Special Investigating Unit continues its probe of the R10.1-million contract. READ: EC Health MEC to appear before Special Tribunal The tribunal sitting commenced on Friday. The SIU has been granted an order interdicting the Eastern Cape health department from paying the company manufacturing the scooters.